Analysis.name: All-cause mortality at day 28
Footnotes: Time point (28 days), participants (WHO 2 to 3, unvaccinated, high risk); intervention (nirmatrelvir/ritonavir); comparator (placebo)
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: Centralized web-based randomization. There are no baseline differences that would suggest a problem with randomization.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: Both participants and those delivering the intervention were not aware of intervention received. The analysis was not appropriate (a per-protocol analysis was used).
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Data for this outcome were reported for all participants of the mITT2 population.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Measurement of the outcome was appropriate. Outcome assessors were not aware of the intervention received.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: The protocol was prospectively registered and the outcome was reported as registered.

Analysis.name: All-cause mortality at day 28
Footnotes: Time point (28 days), participants (WHO 2 to 4, high risk, 25% vaccinated); nirmatrelvir/ritonavir vs SoC
Bias.arising.from.the.randomization.proc: Centralized web-based randomization. There are no baseline differences that would suggest a problem with randomization.
Bias.due.to.deviations.from.intended.int: Participants were aware of intervention received; those delivering the intervention were not. The analysis was appropriate (all participants were analyzed as randomized).
Bias.due.to.missing.outcome.data.support: Data for this outcome were reported for all participants of the study population.
Bias.in.measurement.of.the.outcome.suppo: Open-label trial; unclear whether the outcome assessor was blinded. However, outcome assessment does not involve judgement.
Bias.in.selection.of.the.reported.result: The protocol was prospectively registered and the outcome was reported as registered.
